SUMMARY:Azure Decoded: Getting Ready for the Migrate & Modernize Summit
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nThe Migrate & Modernize Summit is where Microsoft brings together the latest thinking on how to move faster on Azure — using AI‑powered\, agentic approaches to modernize infrastructure\, databases\, and applications.\n\nIn this Azure Decoded episode\, you’ll get a sneak peek at what’s coming: the key themes you’ll hear across Summit keynotes and breakouts\, the real‑world migration and modernization scenarios being spotlighted\, and why this event matters if you’re planning your next move to Azure. We’ll also highlight the skilling opportunities connected to the Summit\, including the Migrate & Modernize Foundations Virtual Training Day\, so you’ll know how to get ready\, what to focus on during the event\, and how to turn what you learn into action afterward.\n\n**What you’ll learn:**\n- What to expect at the Migrate & Modernize Summit — key themes like agentic AI\, Azure Copilot\, Azure Migrate\, and modernization pathways across compute\, data\, and apps.\n- How Microsoft approaches migration and modernization today — from assessment and planning to modernization\, security\, and optimization after the move.\n- How to skill up before and after the Summit — including how the Migrate & Modernize Foundations VTD and learning paths help turn Summit insights into hands‑on capability.\n\n-------------------------------------------------------\n[Explore the Learn Path](https://learn.microsoft.com/plans/j2j1fz78ndwp8m/&wt.mc_id=meetup_26841_webpage_reactor)\n[Azure Skilling - Build Your Azure Migrate and Modernize Skills](https://azure.github.io/MigrateModernizeSkilling/)\n[Microsoft Azure Summit: Migrate and Modernize with Agentic AI](https://www.microsoft.com/events/launch-events/migrate-and-modernize-summit?msockid=0a79b602dee169e70531a109dfa968ea/&wt.mc_id=meetup_26841_webpage_reactor)\n\n📌 This session is a part of a series! Learn more [**here**](https://developer.microsoft.com/reactor/series/S-1644/?wt.mc_id=meetup_S-1644_webpage_reactor)
